This paper discusses a method for reasoning about Bayesian network classifiers, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for converting classifiers into Ordered Decision Diagrams (ODDs) and characterizing discrepancies between classifiers. Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical and experimental properties of the algorithm, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
